法規內容.條文內容:
The functions of the Center are as follows:
1.To evaluate the information of disease surveillance, to formulate and promote disease control response policies;
2.To consolidate and integrate resources, facilities and personnel of organizations (institutions) concerned needed for meeting disease control responses;
3.To conduct matters concerning news releases, information and education, use of mass media with priority, control of entry and exit of country (border), house quarantine, liaison and cooperation with international organizations, control of airports and harbors, expropriation of transportation means, cleaning and disinfection of public environments, labor security and sanitation, control of communicable diseases common to humans and animals, and other necessary control measures against epidemic situations.
